.<br />\nIn IFrame mode the plugin has no problems. I use:</p>\n<p>Wordpress: 3.0.2<br />\nLike-Button-Plugin-For-Wordpress Plugin: 4.2.5.1<br />\nPlugin settings: XFBML<br />\nTheme: <a href=\"http://www.wp-templates.com/free-wp-tem\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.wp-templates.com/free-wp-tem</a> ... ektra.html</p>\n<p>Problem:</p>\n<p>E.g in single view, the Javascript is included BEFORE the &#60;body&#62; tag. And that is wrong!</p>\n<pre><code>&#60;div id=&#34;fb-root&#34;&#62;&#60;/div&#62;\n&#60;script&#62;\n  window.fbAsyncInit = function() {\n    FB.init({appId: &#039;MY_APP_ID&#039;, status: true, cookie: true,\n             xfbml: true});\n  };\n  (function() {\n    var e = document.createElement(&#039;script&#039;);\n   e.type = &#039;text/javascript&#039;;\n    e.src = document.location.protocol +\n      &#039;//connect.facebook.net/de_DE/all.js&#039;;\n     e.async = true;\n    document.getElementById(&#039;fb-root&#039;).appendChild(e);\n  }());\n&#60;/script&#62;\n\n&#60;/head&#62;\n&#60;body&#62;\n...</code></pre>\n<p>What can I do to solve this problem?</p>\n<p>Cheers</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/like-button-plugin-for-wordpress/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/like-button-plugin-for-wordpress/</a>\n</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"phlegx\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:10;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"\n			\n			\n			\n			\n			\n			\n					\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"Andreas on \"[Plugin: Like-Button-Plugin-For-Wordpress] fb_xd_fragment\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xm